Sentencas: A three-dimensional hexagonal gadolinium-doped ceria (GDC) interlayer is fabricated to enhance the cathodic surface area of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Three-dimensional hexagonal GDC interlayer for area enhancement of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: By using modified nanosphere lithography method, 3-D nanostructure is successfully fabricated.
Titulo: Three-dimensional hexagonal GDC interlayer for area enhancement of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: As a result of the nanostructuring, the 3-D hexagonal GDC interlayer has a 70% increase in cathodic surface area.
Titulo: Three-dimensional hexagonal GDC interlayer for area enhancement of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy reveals a 2-fold decrease in the electrode resistance compared with a plane cell, resulting in a current-voltage behavior with a 60% higher peak power density.
Titulo: Three-dimensional hexagonal GDC interlayer for area enhancement of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The superior electrode reaction is attributed to the large surface area (similar to 1.7 times larger) due to the 3-D hexagonal cathodic interlayer.
Titulo: Three-dimensional hexagonal GDC interlayer for area enhancement of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This novel fabrication method can be applied to almost all kinds of LT-SOFC structures, including large-scale and substrate-supported platforms, and thereby it will contribute to commercializing LT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Three-dimensional hexagonal GDC interlayer for area enhancement of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
